urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.135#Either the great-hearted Achaians shall give me a new prize
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.136#chosen according to my desire to atone for the girl lost,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.137#or else if they will not give me one I myself shall take her,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.138#your own prize, or that of Aias, or that of Odysseus,
