urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.140#Still, these are things we shall deliberate again hereafter.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.141#Come, now, we must haul a black ship down to the bright sea,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.142#and assemble rowers enough for it, and put on board it
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.143#the hecatomb, and the girl herself, Chryseis of the fair cheeks,
