urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.163#Never, when the Achaians sack some well-founded citadel
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.164#of the Trojans, do I have a prize that is equal to your prize.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.165#Always the greater part of the painful fighting is the work of
