urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.245#Thus spoke Peleus' son and dashed to the ground the sceptre
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.246#studded with golden nails, and sat down again. But Atreides
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.247#raged still on the other side, and between them Nestor
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.248#the fair-spoken rose up, the lucid speaker of Pylos,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.249#from whose lips the streams of words ran sweeter than honey.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.250#In his time two generations of mortal men had perished,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.251#those who had grown up with him and they who had been born to
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.252#these in sacred Pylos, and he was king in the third age.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.253#He in kind intention toward both stood forth and addressed them:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.254#'Oh, for shame. Great sorrow comes on the land of Achaia.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.255#Now might Priam and the sons of Priam in truth be happy,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.256#and all the rest of the Trojans be visited in their hearts with gladness,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.257#were they to hear all this wherein you two are quarrelling,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.258#you, who surpass all Danaans in council, in fighting.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.259#Yet be persuaded. Both of you are younger than I am.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.260#Yes, and in my time I have dealt with better men than
