urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.262#yet have I seen nor shall see again such men as these were,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.263#men like Peirithoös, and Dryas, shepherd of the people,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.264#Kaineus and Exadios, godlike Polyphemos,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.265#or Theseus, Aigeus' son, in the likeness of the immortals.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.266#These were the strongest generation of earth-born mortals,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.267#the strongest, and they fought against the strongest, the beast men
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.268#living within the mountains, and terribly they destroyed them.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.269#I was of the company of these men, coming from Pylos,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.270#a long way from a distant land, since they had summoned me.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.271#And I fought single-handed, yet against such men no one
