urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.273#these listened to the counsels I gave and heeded my bidding.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.274#Do you also obey, since to be persuaded is better.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.275#You, great man that you are, yet do not take the girl away
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.276#but let her be, a prize as the sons of the Achaians gave her
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.277#first. Nor, son of Peleus, think to match your strength with
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.278#the king, since never equal with the rest is the portion of honour
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.279#of the sceptred king to whom Zeus gives magnificence. Even
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.280#though you are the stronger man, and the mother who bore you was immortal,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.281#yet is this man greater who is lord over more than you rule.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.282#Son of Atreus, give up your anger; even I entreat you
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.283#to give over your bitterness against Achilleus, he who
