urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.285#Then in answer again spoke powerful Agamemnon:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.286#'Yes, old sir, all this you have said is fair and orderly.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.287#Yet here is a man who wishes to be above all others,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.288#who wishes to hold power over all, and to be lord of
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.289#all, and give them their orders, yet I think one will not obey him.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.290#And if the everlasting gods have made him a spearman,
