urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.292#Then looking at him darkly brilliant Achilleus answered him:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.293#'So must I be called of no account and a coward
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.294#if I must carry out every order you may happen to give me.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.295#Tell other men to do these things, but give me no more
