urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.301#ship, you shall take nothing away against my pleasure.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.302#Come, then, only try it, that these others may see also;
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.303#instantly your own black blood will stain my spearpoint.'
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.304#So these two after battling in words of contention
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.305#stood up, and broke the assembly beside the ships of the Achaians.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.306#Peleus' son went back to his balanced ships and his shelter
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.307#with Patroklos, Menoitios' son, and his own companions.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:1.308#But the son of Atreus drew a fast ship down to the water
