urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:4.78#in such likeness Pallas Athene swept flashing earthward
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:4.79#and plunged between the two hosts; and amazement seized the beholders,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:4.80#Trojans, breakers of horses, and strong-greaved Achaians.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:4.81#And thus they would speak to each other, each looking at the man next him:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:4.82#'Surely again there will be evil war and terrible
