urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:4.158#Still the oaths and the blood of the lambs shall not be called vain,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:4.159#the unmixed wine poured and the right hands we trusted.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:4.160#If the Olympian at once has not finished this matter,
