urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.469#terrified as he saw the bronze and the crest with its horse-hair,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.470#nodding dreadfully, as he thought, from the peak of the helmet.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.471#Then his beloved father laughed out, and his honoured mother,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.472#and at once glorious Hektor lifted from his head the helmet
