urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.482#So speaking he set his child again in the arms of his beloved
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.483#wife, who took him back again to her fragrant bosom
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.484#smiling in her tears; and her husband saw, and took pity upon her,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.485#and stroked her with his hand, and called her by name and spoke to her:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.486#'Poor Andromache! Why does your heart sorrow so much for me?
