urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.500#So they mourned in his house over Hektor while he was living
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.501#still, for they thought he would never again come back from the fighting
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.502#alive, escaping the Achaian hands and their violence.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:6.503#But Paris in turn did not linger long in his high house,
