urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:7.21#from his seat on Pergamos, where he planned that the Trojans should conquer.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:7.22#These two then encountered each other beside the oak tree,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:7.23#and speaking first the son of Zeus, lord Apollo, addressed her:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:7.24#'What can be your desire this time, o daughter of great Zeus,
