urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:7.43#He spoke, nor failed to persuade the goddess grey-eyed Athene.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:7.44#Now Helenos, Priam's beloved son, gathered into his heart their
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:7.45#deliberation, and all that pleased the musing divinities.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:7.46#He went on his way and stood beside Hektor and spoke a word to him:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:7.47#'Hektor, o son of Priam and equal of Zeus in counsel,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:7.48#would you now be persuaded by me, for I am your brother?
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:7.49#Make the rest of the Trojans sit down, and all the Achaians,
