urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:11.377#but struck the flat of the right foot, and the shaft driven clean through
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:11.378#stuck in the ground. Then Alexandros, laughing merrily,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:11.379#sprang from his hiding-place and cried out his speech of triumph:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:11.380#'You are hit, and my arrow flew not in vain. How I wish
