urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.51#did, and no longer will fight for me by the grounded vessels.'
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.52#Then answered him in turn the Gerenian horseman Nestor:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.53#'All these things have been brought to fulfilment, nor in any other
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.54#way could even Zeus who thunders on high accomplish it.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.55#For the wall has gone down in which we put our trust, that it
