urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.64#Then in turn the lord of men Agamemnon spoke to him:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.65#'Nestor, since now they are fighting beside the grounded vessels
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.66#and the wall we built has done us no good, nor the ditch either
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.67#where the Danaans endured so much, and their hearts were hopeful
