urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.188#she went out from the chamber, and called aside Aphrodite
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.189#to come away from the rest of the gods, and spoke a word to her:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.190#'Would you do something for me, dear child, if I were to ask you?
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.191#Or would you refuse it? Are you forever angered against me
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.192#because I defend the Danaans, while you help the Trojans?'
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:14.193#Then the daughter of Zeus, Aphrodite, answered her: 'Hera,
