urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.60#Still, we will let all this be a thing of the past; and it was not
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.61#in my heart to be angry forever; and yet I have said
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.62#I would not give over my anger until that time came
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.63#when the fighting with all its clamour came up to my own ships.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.64#So do you draw my glorious armour about your shoulders;
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.65#lead the Myrmidons whose delight is battle into the fighting,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.66#if truly the black cloud of the Trojans has taken position
