urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.70#boldly; because they do not see the face of my helmet
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.71#glaring close; or else they would run and cram full of dead men
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.72#the water-courses; if powerful Agamemnon treated me
