urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.93#for fear some one of the everlasting gods on Olympos
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.94#might crush you. Apollo who works from afar loves these people
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.95#dearly. You must turn back once you bring the light of salvation
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.96#to the ships, and let the others go on fighting in the flat land.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.97#Father Zeus, Athene and Apollo, if only
