urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.650#should kill him with the bronze, and strip the armour away from his shoulders,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.651#or whether to increase the steep work of fighting for more men.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.652#In the division of his heart this way seemed best to him,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:16.653#for the strong henchman of Achilleus, the son of Peleus,
