urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.233#with the weariless bronze put on about our bodies. Let one not
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.234#wait longing for any other summons to stir on the people.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.235#This summons now shall be an evil on anyone left behind
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.236#by the ships of the Argives. Therefore let us drive on together
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.237#and wake the bitter war god on the Trojans, breakers of horses.'
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.238#He spoke, and went away with the sons of glorious Nestor,
