urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.255#to Zeus, prayed, while all the Argives stayed fast at their places
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.256#in silence and in order of station, and listened to their king.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.257#He spoke before them in prayer gazing into the wide sky:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.258#'Let Zeus first be my witness, highest of the gods and greatest,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.259#and Earth, and Helios the Sun, and Furies, who underground
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.260#avenge dead men, when any man has sworn to a falsehood,
