urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.262#on pretext to go to bed with her, or for any other
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.263#reason, but she remained, not singled out, in my shelter.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.264#If any of this is falsely sworn, may the gods give me many
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.265#griefs, all that they inflict on those who swear falsely before them.'
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.266#So he spoke, and with pitiless bronze he cut the boar's throat.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.267#Talthybios whirled the body about, and threw it in the great reach
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.268#of the grey sea, to feed the fishes. Meanwhile Achilleus
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.269#stood up among the battle-fond Achaians, and spoke to them:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.270#'Father Zeus, great are the delusions with which you visit men.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.271#Without you, the son of Atreus could never have stirred so
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.272#the heart inside my breast, nor taken the girl away from me
