urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.331#so that in a fast black ship you could take my son back
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.332#from Skyros to Phthia, and show him all my possessions,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.333#my property, my serving men, my great high-roofed house.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.334#For by this time I think that Peleus must altogether
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.335#have perished, or still keeps a little scant life in sorrow
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:19.336#for the hatefulness of old age and because he waits ever from me
