urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.71#and then lie down in my courts. For a young man all is decorous
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.72#when he is cut down in battle and torn with the sharp bronze, and lies there
