urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.326#brilliant Achilleus drove the spear as he came on in fury,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.327#and clean through the soft part of the neck the spearpoint was driven.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.328#Yet the ash spear heavy with bronze did not sever the windpipe,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.329#so that Hektor could still make exchange of words spoken.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.330#But he dropped in the dust, and brilliant Achilleus vaunted above him:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.331#'Hektor, surely you thought as you killed Patroklos you would be
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.332#safe, and since I was far away you thought nothing of me,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.333#o fool, for an avenger was left, far greater than he was,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.334#behind him and away by the hollow ships. And it was I;
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.335#and I have broken your strength; on you the dogs and the vultures
