urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.344#But looking darkly at him swift-footed Achilleus answered:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.345#'No more entreating of me, you dog, by knees or parents.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.346#I wish only that my spirit and fury would drive me
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.347#to hack your meat away and eat it raw for the things that
