urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.395#He spoke, and now thought of shameful treatment for glorious Hektor.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.396#In both of his feet at the back he made holes by the tendons
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:22.397#in the space between ankle and heel, and drew thongs of ox-hide through them,
