urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.650#May the gods, for what you have done for me, give you great happiness.'
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.651#He spoke, and Peleides went back among the great numbers
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.652#of Achaians assembled, when he had listened to all the praise spoken
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.653#by Neleus' son, and set forth the prizes for the painful boxing.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.654#He led out into the field and tethered there a hard-working
