urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.671#ever, that a man could be a master in every endeavour.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.672#For I'tell you this straight out, and it will be a thing accomplished.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.673#I will smash his skin apart and break his bones on each other.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.674#Let those who care for him wait nearby in a huddle about him
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.675#to carry him out, after my fists have beaten him under.'
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.676#So he spoke, and all of them stayed stricken to silence.
