urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.704#But for the beaten man he set in their midst a woman
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.705#skilled in much work of her hands, and they rated her at four oxen.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.706#He stood upright and spoke his word out among the Argives:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.707#'Rise up, two who would endeavour this prize.' So he spoke
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.708#and presently there rose up huge Telamonian Aias,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.709#and resourceful Odysseus rose, who was versed in every advantage.
