urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.717#bright red with blood, as both of them kept up their hard efforts
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.718#for success and the prize of the wrought tripod. Neither Odysseus
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.wheng:23.719#was able to bring Aias down or throw him to the ground, nor
